{"TopicId":164353,"ForumId":16,"TopicTitle":"Disable auto-crew?","CreatedByName":"Targa","CreatedById":116596,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-08-12T20:52:13Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Targa","CreatedById":116596,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-08-12T20:52:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs there still no way to stop the game from automatically sticking Jeb in the pilot seat of every ship I launch? (other than manually editing the crew in \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003EVAB\u003C/abbr\u003E)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Tex_NL","CreatedById":58254,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-08-12T21:02:02Z","Content":"\n\u003Ciframe data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/159299-13-crew-rr-crew-rest-rotation/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\u003Ciframe data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/127313-13-bettercrewassignment-v131-smarter-by-default-remembers-your-choices-no-ui/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Kerbal101","CreatedById":157058,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-08-12T21:15:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/55485-12x-kerbal-crew-manifest-v0640-dec-30th-2016/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n(works in 1.3)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Spricigo","CreatedById":166502,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-08-13T02:51:26Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI used Better Crew Assignment for a while and is one of these mods that should be stock.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe only reason I removed BCA is to experiment CrewR\u0026amp;R, which supposely is not compatible. I\u0027m still getting used to cR\u0026amp;R but so far I liked.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIMHO both can solve your issue, the choice is\u00A0a matter of taste.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Rocket In My Pocket","CreatedById":154640,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-08-13T12:11:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAs far as stock goes, just don\u0027t make the command module/cockpit the root part/first part you place and it won\u0027t be auto assigned a Kerbal.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-08-13T12:11:16Z\u0022 title=\u002208/13/2017 12:11  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003EAugust 13, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by Rocket In My Pocket\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Tex_NL","CreatedById":58254,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-08-13T12:17:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223147294\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022164353\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221502626263\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022154640\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Rocket In My Pocket\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 minutes ago, Rocket In My Pocket said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n... and it won\u0027t be auto assigned a Kerbal.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nInstead it will be assigned with NO Kerbal.\u003Cbr\u003E\nNo Kerbal is just as frustrating as the wrong Kerbal.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Rocket In My Pocket","CreatedById":154640,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-08-13T12:18:58Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223147300\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022164353\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221502626629\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002258254\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Tex_NL\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, Tex_NL said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nInstead it will be assigned with NO Kerbal.\u003Cbr\u003E\nNo Kerbal is just as frustrating as the wrong Kerbal.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAgreed, this can be just as frustrating depending on what it is you are trying to do. Lol.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe \u003Cabbr title=\u00221. Original Post(er). The first post in a thread, or the person who posted it. 2. Overpowered. A part or mechanic that upsets game balance by being too powerful.\u0022\u003EOP\u003C/abbr\u003E wasn\u0027t specific but if he\u0027s making a rescue ship with a probe core and wants the seat left empty, it\u0027s a valid solution.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}